President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. These include Francine Berman and Deborah Willis as members of the National Council on the Humanities, Mario Cordero as Commissioner of the Federal Maritime Commission, Bella Dinh-Zarr as a member of the National Transportation Safety Board, Rear Admiral Earl L. Gay as Deputy Director of the Office of Personnel Management, Paul A. Folmsbee as Ambassador to the Republic of Mali, and Mary Catherine Phee as Ambassador to the Republic of South Sudan. President Obama commended these individuals for their knowledge and dedication and expressed his gratitude for their willingness to take on these important roles.